00:56.230 --> 00:59.059
- Daddy!

01:07.023 --> 01:08.024
My babies.

01:08.503 --> 01:11.071
-Mom? Mom!
- My babies, help!

01:14.509 --> 01:16.119
Mommy, come here.
There's a fire!

01:16.163 --> 01:17.381
There's a fire in there!

01:20.776 --> 01:22.430
Call the fire department!

01:26.608 --> 01:28.610
Yes. Hello,
I'd like to report fire.

01:30.264 --> 01:33.093
Yes, it's 1213 West 11th Street.

01:37.184 --> 01:38.968
Uh, yeah.

01:39.011 --> 01:40.970
It's my-- It's my neighbor's.

01:44.626 --> 01:47.716
Yes, there is...
There's babies in there.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.110
I don't know.

01:56.028 --> 01:57.552
There's been an explosion.

02:00.990 --> 02:02.165
Oh, my God.

02:06.952 --> 02:08.215
Please, God.

02:09.128 --> 02:11.305
-Please, let them be all right.

02:11.566 --> 02:13.698
Please, please, God.

02:14.786 --> 02:16.136
I'm sorry.

03:15.064 --> 03:16.413
It didn't start in here.

03:20.678 --> 03:22.114
What a sick puppy.

03:30.775 --> 03:32.037
Well, lookie here.

03:33.125 --> 03:34.649
He didn't take no chances.

03:43.353 --> 03:44.354
Check this out.

03:47.401 --> 03:48.837
Crazed glass.

03:53.363 --> 03:54.451
Kids' room.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.456
Piece of shit waited
'till they were asleep.

04:05.157 --> 04:07.595
So, he pours the accelerant
here.

04:08.465 --> 04:12.687
-And it flashes over.
-It goes straight out the door.

04:13.644 --> 04:15.777
-Right along that baseboard.
-Yup.

04:16.908 --> 04:18.170
Onto the porch.

04:19.954 --> 04:21.086
Son of a bitch.

04:21.783 --> 04:22.827
We'll nail him.

04:27.484 --> 04:29.356
Thank you for coming down,
folks.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.662
-I know how hard this must be.

04:32.184 --> 04:35.797
This is Mr. Fogg, Mr. Vasquez.
They're investigating the fire.

04:37.668 --> 04:38.887
Our condolences.

04:39.670 --> 04:40.976
Y'all find out anything?

04:41.237 --> 04:42.760
We're still trying to find
our way.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.894
Think you might be able to help
us figure out a couple things.

04:46.155 --> 04:47.156
Of course.

04:48.984 --> 04:50.290
It's Stacy, right?

04:52.204 --> 04:54.468
Now, you weren't in the house
at the time of the fire.

04:54.511 --> 04:55.512
That's right.

04:56.687 --> 04:58.298
She works nights sometimes,

04:58.341 --> 04:59.995
stopped on the way home
from work.

05:02.911 --> 05:04.565
Whereabouts was it you stopped,
darling?

05:09.744 --> 05:13.095
I stopped at the Salvation Army
to get the babies some presents.

05:16.707 --> 05:19.319
-At 9:00 in the morning?
-Well, Christmas is coming

05:19.362 --> 05:21.669
-and we're broke, so...
-Of course.

05:23.061 --> 05:24.324
How about the day before?

05:25.716 --> 05:27.370
Anything unusual happen?

05:29.677 --> 05:30.678
No, sir.

05:45.301 --> 05:46.389
Hey, there.

05:47.259 --> 05:48.870
How are my precious ladies?

05:49.479 --> 05:51.176
Ooh, why are you crying?

05:52.526 --> 05:54.136
They've been crying all fucking
morning.

05:54.179 --> 05:55.355
You girls are lucky.

05:56.965 --> 05:58.401
If your mama wasn't so pretty,
you three wouldn't be here.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.968
Oh, you fucking stink.

06:00.229 --> 06:01.970
What, do you think you can
just stay out all night

06:02.013 --> 06:03.275
and then come home
and sweet-talk me?

06:03.319 --> 06:04.755
Honey, I had a couple o' drinks.

06:05.277 --> 06:07.715
I already got one DUI,
so I stopped at Mikey's.

06:10.631 --> 06:12.415
-What?
-Nothing.

06:15.897 --> 06:16.985
Have at it.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.338
So, that night,
you went to work?

06:24.340 --> 06:26.560
Yeah, I work nights.
We need the money.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.605
And you stayed at home
with the kids?

06:28.649 --> 06:30.564
-You do that a lot?
-That's right.

06:31.913 --> 06:34.132
I guess I'm one of them
stay-at-home dads

06:34.176 --> 06:35.569
everybody's talking about.

06:40.269 --> 06:42.402
There's another dinner in the
oven if you're hungry.

06:44.273 --> 06:45.448
Who is it this time, Todd?

06:45.492 --> 06:46.406
Who was who?

06:48.190 --> 06:49.452
I already told you

06:49.496 --> 06:51.541
-where I was last night.
-You ain't told me shit.

06:51.585 --> 06:53.500
You think I'm stupid?
What the fuck is this?

06:53.935 --> 06:55.240
Baby, you're the one that said

06:55.284 --> 06:56.633
you don't wanna have
no more children.

06:56.677 --> 06:58.896
Then what's it doing in your
wallet, you bastard?

06:58.940 --> 06:59.810
I don't know.

07:01.377 --> 07:02.987
-I thought maybe surprise sex--
-You're such a fucking liar.

07:03.031 --> 07:05.207
I could smell the bitch on you
when you walked in this morning.

07:05.250 --> 07:08.210
-I'm not lying to you, honey.
-Mm-hmm. You ain't worth shit

07:08.253 --> 07:09.820
-for a husband.
-Bitch!

07:10.647 --> 07:13.041
I'm here every goddamn day
taking care of these kids.

07:13.084 --> 07:14.346
Oh, yeah? And why's that?

07:16.000 --> 07:17.393
Why are you here every goddamn
day taking care of these kids?

07:17.437 --> 07:20.222
Because you don't have
a fucking job, that's why.

07:20.265 --> 07:21.963
Because you are a fucking loser.

07:22.006 --> 07:23.747
Better shut the fuck up
that shit right now--

07:23.791 --> 07:25.140
Or what?

07:25.183 --> 07:26.750
-I swear to God, woman.
-You hit me again? Go on.

07:27.490 --> 07:29.100
Oh, yeah, that's right. You
can't hit me.

07:29.144 --> 07:30.885
Because if you do,
then I can't go to work,

07:30.928 --> 07:33.235
and I can't make you money
to go out drinking and fucking

07:33.278 --> 07:34.802
whatever the fuck else you do.

07:39.328 --> 07:41.678
So, Stacy went to work that
night and you just, uh,

07:41.983 --> 07:42.984
stayed in bed?

07:47.249 --> 07:48.250
Yes, sir.

07:48.598 --> 07:49.904
Had a few beers, maybe?

07:52.863 --> 07:53.864
No.

07:55.300 --> 07:56.214
Reckon your kids
sleep pretty sound?

07:57.389 --> 07:58.347
Usually.

08:01.219 --> 08:02.438
And then that night?

08:03.570 --> 08:04.745
It was morning.

08:06.224 --> 08:08.270
I was asleep, so I thought I
was dreaming at first.

08:08.313 --> 08:09.576
- Daddy!
-But then I realized

08:09.619 --> 08:12.013
I could hear Amber screaming,
"Daddy! Daddy!"

08:13.318 --> 08:14.581
Daddy!

08:17.845 --> 08:19.368
Everything was full of smoke.

08:19.411 --> 08:21.413
I couldn't see nothing
but black.

08:21.457 --> 08:22.676
It smelled like it did

08:22.719 --> 08:24.504
when the microwave
blowed up last month.

08:24.547 --> 08:26.549
-Fires, lights popping.
- Daddy!

08:26.593 --> 08:27.637
Girls!

08:27.985 --> 08:29.900
So, I made it to their room
and...

08:31.815 --> 08:33.774
I had to kick through
the child-proof thing.

08:37.125 --> 08:39.562
I never felt anything
so hot in my life.

08:42.217 --> 08:44.654
I thought I'd found Amber,
but she was gone.

08:44.698 --> 08:45.742
Amber.

08:48.658 --> 08:49.659
Girls.

08:50.921 --> 08:51.922
Amber!

08:52.662 --> 08:53.750
Girls!

08:54.751 --> 08:56.448
I couldn't take the heat, so...

08:57.275 --> 08:59.582
I had to get outside, catch my
breath.

09:03.891 --> 09:05.022
That's when I hollered out

09:05.066 --> 09:07.024
for my neighbor
to call emergency.

09:16.425 --> 09:18.645
Can you think of why anyone
would wanna hurt your family?

09:18.949 --> 09:19.950
No, sir.

09:26.217 --> 09:27.697
We had three
of the prettiest babies

09:27.741 --> 09:29.220
anybody could've asked for.

09:30.613 --> 09:33.398
Off and on, we'd fight
and break up for a while,

09:33.442 --> 09:36.010
but it was always the babies
that brought us back together.

09:36.837 --> 09:39.056
Neither of us could've lived
without them kids.

09:42.277 --> 09:44.932
Sometimes, I wish Amber
had never woke me up.

09:49.676 --> 09:51.852
You know, Todd,
you've been in trouble before.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.942
-Yes, sir.
-A couple of those times

09:54.985 --> 09:56.596
when we asked you what happened,

09:56.639 --> 09:59.250
you didn't exactly tell the
truth, isn't that so?

10:00.556 --> 10:01.601
No, sir.

10:03.211 --> 10:04.734
But you're telling the truth
now?

10:04.778 --> 10:05.692
Yes, sir.

10:10.784 --> 10:14.178
Just as Jesus, the Lamb of God,
was taken too soon,

10:14.222 --> 10:16.528
so too were these three
innocents,

10:16.572 --> 10:18.705
taken back to the bosom
of the Lord.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.708
How else are we to understand

10:21.751 --> 10:25.537
the loss of Amber, Karmen,
and Kameron.

10:31.282 --> 10:34.111
Do you wanna stop somewhere
and maybe get...

10:35.069 --> 10:36.766
-something to eat?
-Cameron Todd Willingham,

10:36.810 --> 10:38.638
I don't wanna hear your voice.

10:39.073 --> 10:40.509
And maybe never again.

10:41.902 --> 10:45.209
-I'm hurting, too, baby--
-Did you hear a word I said?

10:45.253 --> 10:47.168
Oh, if you're gonna start
demonizing me,

10:47.211 --> 10:48.560
-speak to me like--
-I'll speak to you

10:48.604 --> 10:50.475
-however I please.
-You will not either.

10:50.737 --> 10:52.390
Baby, if we're ever gonna get
through this,

10:52.434 --> 10:54.349
-we gotta work together on--
-Stop the car.

10:54.784 --> 10:56.438
Stop the car,
let me out of the car.

10:56.481 --> 10:58.701
-Why? Why, what's the matter--
-Stop the car!

10:58.745 --> 11:01.269
-I won't stop the car--
-Stop the fucking car, Todd!

11:01.312 --> 11:03.663
-Tell me why.
-Let me out of the car!

11:03.706 --> 11:06.100
Stop the fucking car, Todd!

11:06.143 --> 11:08.450
-Let me out of the car!

11:08.493 --> 11:10.017
-Stop the fucking car!

11:10.060 --> 11:11.671
Those were my babies!

11:11.888 --> 11:15.196
Those were my babies
and you didn't save them!

11:15.239 --> 11:17.328
They were my babies!

11:17.764 --> 11:19.417
My babies, Todd!

11:32.909 --> 11:33.780
Driver!

11:35.259 --> 11:36.870
Exit the vehicle, put your hands
up where I can see them.

11:36.913 --> 11:38.001
Do it now!

11:41.570 --> 11:43.311
Turn around, face away from me.

11:43.354 --> 11:45.356
Interlace your hands
behind your head.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.098
Do not look back.

11:54.104 --> 11:55.497
Cameron Todd Willingham...

11:57.107 --> 11:58.630
you're under arrest for murder.

11:58.674 --> 12:00.241
-Murder?
- You come with me.

12:00.284 --> 12:02.025
-Who did I kill?
-Come on.

12:02.069 --> 12:03.679
We'll talk about it
at the station.

12:05.812 --> 12:07.596
Let's go, Todd.
You know the way.

12:08.902 --> 12:10.773
I only just buried them, Marty.

12:12.732 --> 12:14.603
This is some fucked up bullshit.

12:15.473 --> 12:16.561
Stand right there.

12:24.308 --> 12:25.353
Let's go.

12:32.882 --> 12:35.058
You're a real piece of shit,
you know that?

12:35.102 --> 12:36.407
Your own kids?

12:36.930 --> 12:39.193
-Jesus, man.
-I didn't do it, Marty.

12:39.236 --> 12:40.542
Fuck you!

12:40.585 --> 12:42.022
Hey, fuck you!

12:46.026 --> 12:47.984
Man, would you get
the fuck down from there?

12:48.028 --> 12:49.290
This ain't no fucking zoo!

12:50.334 --> 12:51.945
Jesus fucking Christ.

12:52.597 --> 12:54.991
You want a banana?
That'll make you calm down?

12:55.949 --> 12:57.515
They ain't gonna throw you no
fucking peanuts,

12:57.559 --> 12:58.647
you know that, right?

12:59.300 --> 13:00.823
Who're you talking to, boy?

13:01.868 --> 13:03.347
I was just talking
to that mullet,

13:03.391 --> 13:04.479
you know,
she's real cute.

13:04.522 --> 13:06.176
She gave me a little wink,
you know.

13:08.700 --> 13:10.659
-This yours?
-Hey.

13:15.229 --> 13:16.143
Yours?

13:29.939 --> 13:30.940
Get up.

13:32.246 --> 13:33.551
Look, I'm good, man.
I was just fucking around.

13:35.379 --> 13:37.120
You ain't gotta take shit
so personal.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.863
You smell like you wanna be left
alone.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.871
If you plead guilty,
you might live.

13:48.915 --> 13:51.091
I'm not confessing
to something I didn't do.

13:52.092 --> 13:53.745
I'll say any goddamn thing
you like,

13:53.789 --> 13:55.660
but I will not say
I killed my own kids.

13:55.704 --> 13:56.923
With the evidence they got,

13:56.966 --> 13:58.533
-they're gonna--
-I'm going to take the stand

13:58.576 --> 14:00.665
and I'm gonna talk to the judge
about it.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.450
Idiot, they will tear you up
on the stand.

14:02.493 --> 14:03.407
Oh, they better.

14:04.582 --> 14:05.670
Boy, you're about as
dumb as you look--

14:05.714 --> 14:06.802
What the fuck is wrong
with you, huh?

14:06.846 --> 14:08.021
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Todd, calm down.

14:08.064 --> 14:09.457
Oh, listen to him!

14:12.329 --> 14:14.157
They wanna kill me? Good.

14:14.854 --> 14:16.638
They better start
digging my grave now,

14:16.681 --> 14:19.467
because I'll die before I say
I killed my own kids.

14:19.510 --> 14:23.558
Boy, I am the only thing between
you and the needle right now.

14:24.341 --> 14:26.213
No way in hell
I'm putting you on that stand.

14:28.084 --> 14:31.827
Good morning,
Texas. This is KZYZ.

14:31.871 --> 14:34.569
The phone lines are burning up.
Let's hear from you.

14:34.612 --> 14:36.527
I never liked him.
I always thought there was

14:36.571 --> 14:37.833
something kind of
off about him,

14:37.877 --> 14:39.182
and it doesn't surprise me
a little bit.

14:39.226 --> 14:40.880
They should fry him.

14:40.923 --> 14:42.098
-He needs to burn in hell.
- What kind of daddy

14:42.142 --> 14:43.578
would kill his own babies
like that?

14:43.621 --> 14:44.666
Things like this
don't happen here.

14:44.709 --> 14:45.667
Hey, I'll shoot him myself.

14:45.710 --> 14:46.886
Boy took three innocent lives.

14:46.929 --> 14:48.322
The only thing I regret is,

14:48.365 --> 14:50.324
we can't kill him
three times over.

14:50.759 --> 14:52.108
Members of the jury,

14:52.152 --> 14:54.023
I'd like you to take a look

14:54.067 --> 14:57.461
at the sweet faces
of these beautiful babies...

14:58.114 --> 15:00.682
Karmen and Kameron,
barely a year old

15:01.074 --> 15:03.598
and already brimming with life.

15:04.425 --> 15:08.168
Little Amber, eagerly waiting
for Santa's visit

15:08.472 --> 15:10.126
in only two days.

15:11.911 --> 15:15.305
Now, I want you to imagine
these little angels...

15:15.349 --> 15:17.829
-...burning in their beds.

15:19.005 --> 15:20.920
This was no arson.

15:22.530 --> 15:23.748
This was murder.

15:25.141 --> 15:28.449
Well, I barely poked my head
out the door when...

15:30.190 --> 15:33.584
he just stood there with
a strange look in his eyes--

15:33.628 --> 15:35.847
-That's total bullshit.
- Shut up.

15:36.587 --> 15:39.503
To the best of your knowledge,
did Todd Willingham

15:39.547 --> 15:42.942
ever make an attempt
to get back in that house?

15:44.421 --> 15:46.510
He was too worried about that
car of his.

15:47.555 --> 15:50.514
He didn't try to save those kids
till the cops showed up.

15:51.385 --> 15:54.518
And it was like he was...
putting on a show.

15:55.563 --> 15:58.740
Fire talks to you,
it does not lie.

15:58.783 --> 16:00.785
Then what did that fire
tell you?

16:00.829 --> 16:04.050
That it was deliberately set
by human hands.

16:06.226 --> 16:07.531
Can you be more specific?

16:09.011 --> 16:11.144
Someone poured gasoline
through those children's room,

16:11.187 --> 16:14.408
even under their bed
in the shape of a pentagram,

16:14.451 --> 16:15.844
the symbol of the devil.

16:17.106 --> 16:18.934
He kept pouring down the hallway
to the front door,

16:19.152 --> 16:21.981
creating a fire barrier,
preventing any escape.

16:24.853 --> 16:27.160
That fire was hotter
than the hinges of hell.

16:27.899 --> 16:30.250
We found evidence
of what we call crazed glass,

16:30.293 --> 16:32.904
another indication it was goosed
by liquid additive.

16:33.253 --> 16:36.734
Worst of all, the refrigerator
was moved to block the backdoor.

16:37.387 --> 16:39.302
Someone made that house
into a death trap.

16:39.694 --> 16:43.872
Inspector Vasquez, how many
arson cases have you worked on?

16:43.915 --> 16:45.917
I reckon more than 1,200 fires.

16:45.961 --> 16:47.484
And to the best
of your knowledge,

16:48.050 --> 16:49.747
have you ever been
mistaken?

16:50.139 --> 16:53.012
Sir, fire does not destroy
evidence, it creates it.

16:53.273 --> 16:55.884
If I've ever been wrong,
it's never been pointed out.

16:57.886 --> 16:59.148
Mr. Horton?

16:59.844 --> 17:00.976
No questions, Your Honor.

17:03.805 --> 17:07.939
Mr. Webb, you shared a cell
with Todd Willingham

17:07.983 --> 17:11.030
at the Navarro County Jail,
is that correct?

17:11.595 --> 17:12.640
Yes, sir.

17:12.944 --> 17:15.817
And what did he tell you
at that time?

17:17.949 --> 17:18.819
Well, he...

17:19.646 --> 17:20.952
He said that...

17:21.910 --> 17:26.132
he came home
and that one of his children

17:26.175 --> 17:29.135
was hurt or even dead
or whatever.

17:29.178 --> 17:31.789
-What?
-And then so, he started--

17:31.833 --> 17:35.141
He decided that he was gonna
cover it up by starting a fire.

17:35.184 --> 17:36.533
Hell no.

17:37.317 --> 17:40.537
Did he tell you who it was
that injured that child?

17:41.408 --> 17:43.018
He did. He said it was his wife.

17:43.453 --> 17:44.498
-What?
-Yeah.

17:44.541 --> 17:46.326
He said she was crying,
yeah,

17:46.369 --> 17:48.197
and carrying on
with such emotion.

17:48.241 --> 17:52.201
He just decided to take some
paper and wad it up,

17:52.245 --> 17:55.204
and then he burnt it in a way
that made it look like

17:55.248 --> 17:57.163
them children was playing
with it and such.

17:57.206 --> 18:00.862
And did Willingham ever threaten
you about telling anybody

18:00.905 --> 18:02.907
-what he had told you?
-Yeah.

18:03.778 --> 18:05.910
He pointed his finger at me
and did like this.

18:05.954 --> 18:07.086
I'll kill you.

18:08.565 --> 18:09.827
-Thank you, Mr. Webb.
-Y'all need to start speaking

18:09.871 --> 18:11.307
some fucking truth around here!

18:11.351 --> 18:12.743
-Calm down. You just sit down.
-I am!

18:12.787 --> 18:13.875
No, no, this is corrupt.

18:13.918 --> 18:15.137
Don't believe that shit.

18:15.181 --> 18:16.530
That shit never happened, Judge.

18:16.573 --> 18:17.792
Control your client.

18:17.835 --> 18:19.054
-Counselor.
- That shit didn't happen.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.926
-Counselor.
-You took an oath, didn't you?

18:21.970 --> 18:23.711
Start speaking some
fucking truth then, boy.

18:23.754 --> 18:26.409
-This is my courtroom, sir.

18:26.453 --> 18:28.933
Mr. Jackson,
call your next witness.

18:29.412 --> 18:33.068
Mr. Evans,
you have firsthand knowledge

18:33.112 --> 18:36.898
of Todd Willingham's history
of violent behavior, don't you?

18:36.941 --> 18:38.029
Yes, sir.

18:38.073 --> 18:39.161
Would you explain to us

18:39.205 --> 18:40.815
what transpired
between the two of you?

18:41.337 --> 18:44.819
I mean, maybe me and Stacy
was flirting a little,

18:45.211 --> 18:46.429
but it ain't mean nothing.

18:47.996 --> 18:51.391
