48:59.632 --> 49:00.633
Hey.

49:01.895 --> 49:03.114
You need some help?

49:05.551 --> 49:06.987
So, are you from around here?

49:11.078 --> 49:12.558
Why'd you stop back there?

49:14.560 --> 49:16.518
Oh, I didn't think you were
dangerous.

49:17.128 --> 49:19.260
Figured I could take you
one on one.

49:22.002 --> 49:23.221
You weren't scared?

49:23.830 --> 49:26.137
-What?
-You weren't scared?

49:27.007 --> 49:28.791
Of you? Why?

49:29.140 --> 49:30.141
Why not?

49:32.665 --> 49:34.536
I guess I just didn't think
about it.

49:35.668 --> 49:37.104
Thank you so much.

49:37.148 --> 49:38.584
Oh, thank you.

49:38.627 --> 49:40.107
Can't you stay a moment more?

49:41.021 --> 49:43.545
You might be just the kind
of person we're looking for.

49:44.503 --> 49:47.549
Oh, you're scared now?

49:48.942 --> 49:52.859
Well, I'm a little weirded out,
to tell you the truth.

49:53.773 --> 49:55.775
-What you want from me?
-Your address.

49:56.471 --> 49:58.821
-What for?
-I wanna send you something.

49:58.865 --> 50:00.562
Oh, you don't need to
send me anything.

50:00.606 --> 50:02.347
Well, I wanna return the favor.

50:02.825 --> 50:05.002
I think you and I were intended
to meet.

50:06.264 --> 50:09.049
So, was she, like,
a crazy person or--

50:09.093 --> 50:10.964
Why did she want
your address?

50:11.312 --> 50:15.447
Well, she said somebody might
wanna write me a letter.

50:15.708 --> 50:17.362
-Who?
-A prisoner.

50:18.798 --> 50:20.495
-What?
-Nothing.

50:20.539 --> 50:23.063
- What?
-Just classic Liz.

50:23.107 --> 50:25.805
-Oh, here we go.
-The abandoned kittens,

50:26.066 --> 50:28.155
the homeless family
at the truck stop.

50:28.199 --> 50:29.504
Oh, my God.

50:29.548 --> 50:31.419
The starving African kids
on TV.

50:31.463 --> 50:34.422
-Okay. Gullible, bleeding heart.
-Oh, I'm not saying that.

50:34.466 --> 50:35.858
You called me St. Liz
for a decade.

50:35.902 --> 50:37.730
Well, that's not what I think.

50:39.123 --> 50:41.603
We're well past lying, George,
aren't we?

50:43.605 --> 50:46.565
So, yesterday, I got a letter.

50:46.608 --> 50:49.307
-Hey, Mom.
-Hey, girl, how was school?

50:50.569 --> 50:51.918
Earth to Julie.

50:52.788 --> 50:55.052
-Sorry?
-Never mind.

50:55.095 --> 50:56.618
-Love you.
-Love you, too.

50:58.359 --> 51:04.061
And it said, "Dear Ms. Gilbert,
I got your address from TCADP.

51:04.104 --> 51:07.803
I was told that you might be
willing to correspond

51:08.369 --> 51:10.458
with someone such as myself."

51:10.502 --> 51:12.808
What is that, the TAD,
whatever?

51:12.852 --> 51:13.983
TCADP.

51:15.289 --> 51:17.030
Texas Coalition
to Abolish the Death Penalty.

51:17.074 --> 51:18.292
How'd you get involved in that?

51:18.336 --> 51:20.729
The lady who asked
for my address.

51:21.382 --> 51:23.689
-You don't listen to me.
-No, I was listening.

51:23.732 --> 51:25.430
-What did he do?
-Never mind.

51:25.473 --> 51:27.649
Oh, come on, Liz
Come on.

51:27.693 --> 51:29.086
Why is he on death row?

51:29.477 --> 51:30.609
He...

51:32.045 --> 51:34.265
He burned down his house
with his kids inside.

51:34.308 --> 51:36.136
-That's charming.

51:36.702 --> 51:39.270
-All right. Here.

51:45.145 --> 51:47.669
So, why exactly
are you doing this?

51:47.713 --> 51:49.280
I didn't say I was doing it.

51:49.323 --> 51:50.803
But you're thinking about it.

51:51.195 --> 51:55.286
Well, can't I just not know?
I don't know.

51:55.329 --> 51:58.593
Isn't looking after one person
with a death sentence enough?

52:02.293 --> 52:04.251
-I'm sorry.

52:06.123 --> 52:10.605
So, are you and the kids okay?
Money and everything.

52:11.606 --> 52:13.086
-Yeah.
-Well, if you need anything,

52:13.130 --> 52:15.393
-just...
-Your check comes on time.

52:16.916 --> 52:18.570
And we talked all that out.

52:20.789 --> 52:22.748
-I failed you, Liz.

52:23.836 --> 52:25.359
And yet, you're here for me.

52:26.578 --> 52:28.449
If thing's were the other way
around,

52:29.102 --> 52:30.625
would I be there for you?

52:32.845 --> 52:34.803
Do we get off that sow
or just admit the truth?

52:38.851 --> 52:39.895
How are you...

52:41.332 --> 52:42.246
really?

52:49.557 --> 52:51.559
-Mama, you forgot the milk.

52:51.603 --> 52:53.692
-I'm going to the market later.
-Okay.

52:53.735 --> 52:55.998
-Mom, what are reading there?
-Letter from a guy in jail

52:56.042 --> 52:57.174
-who kills babies.
-Julie.

52:58.653 --> 52:59.915
What, are you writing
a play about him or something?

52:59.959 --> 53:02.527
No, sweetie, there's a man
who is in prison--

53:02.570 --> 53:04.616
-He wants Mama to visit him.
-Seriously?

53:05.269 --> 53:07.793
